[{"id":"VR839899","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two incomplete triangles. One triangle is white, outlined with a black border, and the other triangle, which looks like it is on top of the first triangle, is a white triangle that has borders that are only apparent because the other shapes in the figure are incomplete where the top triangle overlaps with them. The top triangle has a black, incomplete circle at each of its three corners. It appears as if the borders of the top triangle are cutting into the circles to complete the borders of the top triangle.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR839899.g02.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Audra is working on a puzzle book and comes across the following figure. Which of the following Gestalt laws would best explain Audraâ€™s perception of the image?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR839899_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">closure</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">similarity</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">proximity</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">continuity</p>"],"answer":0}]